As they have no possessive pronouns, mine, thine‚ his, the want of them is supplied in every noun, by the addition or alteration of various letters. Amongst the Abipones a great diffi- culty is occasioned by the various changes of the letters, especially in the second person. Take these examples. Neu), a father indeter- minately. Vita, my father.
